Edition:
Quote: Angelica Gingidum (The Native Aniseed.) ... The whole plant is highly aromatic. It is greedily eaten bysheep, and though originally very abundant, is often almost exterminated by them in accessible places. The plant is known to shepherds and runholders  as <i>Aniseed. </i>
