Date: 0/0/1954
Source: Te Raka
Author: MACFARLANE
Vol / Page: 40
Edition:
Quote: The outstanding plant in these preserves and the one that disappeared as the deer came along was aniseed. We do know that it was common everywhere once and gave a bright sheen, when in flower, to the whole of NorthCanterbury; but sheep appeared to relish it and, being a soft plant with no defence, it has vanished except on isolated bluffs and crannies.
